<html ><head ><meta charset="UTF-8"  /><meta name="author" content="Martin Walther - @tinuwalther"  /><meta name="keywords" content="Pode, PSHTML, PowerShell, Mermaid Diagram"  /><meta name="description" content="Builds beatuifull HTML-Files with PSHTML from native PowerShell-Scripts"  /><link href="\assets\BootStrap\bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"  /><link href="\assets\style\style.css" rel="stylesheet"  /><script src="\assets\BootStrap\bootstrap.bundle.min.js"  ></script><title >#PSXi SQLite Data</title><link rel="icon" href="/assets/img/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon"  /></head><Body ><header ><div Style="padding:15; background-color:#033b63" Class="jumbotron text-center" Id="j1"  ><p ><h1 >#PSXi SQLite Data</h1></p><p >I ♥ PS Pode > This is an example for using pode and PSHTML, requested by API</p></div></header><Section Id="section"  ><nav Class="navbar navbar-expand-sm bg-dark navbar-dark sticky-top"  ><div Class="container-fluid"  ><a href="/" Class="navbar-brand" Target="_self"  >»HOME</a><button Class="navbar-toggler" data-bs-target="#collapsibleNavbar" data-bs-toggle="collapse" type="button"  ><span Class="navbar-toggler-icon"  ></span></button><div Id="collapsibleNavbar" Class="collapse navbar-collapse"  ><ul Class="navbar-nav"  ><li Class="nav-item"  ><a href="https://github.com/jdhitsolutions/MySQLite/" Class="nav-link" Target="_blank"  >mySQLite</a></li><li Class="nav-item"  ><a href="/help" Class="nav-link" Target="_self"  >Help</a></li></ul></div></div></nav><div Id="Content" Class="Container"  ><h1 Style="color:#212529"  >VMware ESXi Host Inventory</h1><p Style="color:#000"  >On load, the page execute the SQL query and generate the table based of D:\github.com\PodePSHTML\db\psxi.db.</p><p Style="color:#000"  >Dynamically created table based on 'SELECT * FROM "classic_ESXiHosts" ORDER BY Notes Desc Limit 3' from the last API request.</p></div><div Id="Content" Class="Container"  ><article Id="SQLite"  >
$($SQLiteDbPath = 'D:\github.com\PodePSHTML\db\psxi.db')
$($SqliteQuery = 'SELECT * FROM "classic_ESXiHosts" ORDER BY Notes Desc Limit 3')
$($SQLiteData = Invoke-MySQLiteQuery -Path $SQLiteDbPath -Query $SqliteQuery);
$($SplatProperties = @{
    TableClass = 'table table-responsive table-striped table-hover'
    TheadClass = 'thead-dark'
    Properties = @('HostName','Version','vCenterServer','Cluster','ConnectionState','Model','PhysicalLocation','Notes')
    }
)
$($SQLiteData | ConvertTo-PSHtmlTable @SplatProperties)
</article></div></Section><pre Style="color:#000"  >Re-builds the page: I ♥ PS > Invoke-WebRequest -Uri http://localhost:8080/api/sqlite -Method Post -Body 'SELECT * FROM "classic_ESXiHosts" Limit 7'</pre></Body><div Style="background-color:#343a40" Class="container-fluid"  ><footer ><div Class="container-fluid"  ><div Class="row align-items-center"  ><div Class="col-md"  ><p ><a href="#" Class="btn-sm btn btn-outline-success" Target="_self"  >I ♥ PS ></a></p></div><div Class="col-md"  ><p >Based on <a href="https://www.powershellgallery.com/packages/Pode" Target="_blank"  >pode</a> and <a href="https://www.powershellgallery.com/packages/PSHTML" Target="_blank"  >PSHTML</a></p></div><div Style="color:#000" Class="col-md"  ><p >Dynamically created at $(Get-Date -f 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss')</p></div></div></div></footer></div></html>
